termnote.p:
The luminous intensity is expressed in candela (cd









=lm⁢sr−1







).

The luminance is expressed in candela per square metre (cd⁢m−2









=lm⁢m−2⁢sr−1







).

The illuminance is expressed in lux (lx









=lm⁢m−2







)

clause.p:
The definition of Kcd relates the unit of luminous flux (lumen, lm









) to the unit of radiant flux (watt, W








) at wavelength λcd. For wavelengths other than λcd, the luminous efficacy is proportional to one of the spectral luminous efficiency functions described in Chapter 4.

The SI unit of luminous intensity is lumen per steradian (lm⁢sr−1







), which is termed candela (cd









).

The SI unit of luminance is lumen per square metre per steradian (lm⁢sr−1⁢m−2







) or candela per square metre (cd⁢m−2









).

The SI unit of illuminance is lumen per square metre (lm⁢m−2







), which is termed lux (lx









).

